Feature: Timeline Feed endpoint (backend-only)

Overview
- Add a new endpoint in `mbooks-quarkus` to serve timeline/news content for infinite scrolling.
- Feed content includes featured movie news and actor news.
- Scope ends at API and data layer; no UI implementation is included in this feature.

Contract IDs
- `CID-MBOOKS-TIMELINE`

Role collaboration
- Implementation: `@backend-dev`, `@database-dev`
- Consumer contract checks: `@frontend-dev`, `@ios-dev`
- Test ownership: `@testing-engineer`
- Security review: `@security-specialist`
- Performance validation: `@performance-engineer`
- Requirement/acceptance alignment: `@business-analyst`

Functional requirements

REQ-TF-1 Endpoint contract
- Method: `GET`
- Path: `/rest/book/timeline-feed`
- Produces: `application/json`
- Query params:
  - `limit` optional integer, default `20`, allowed range `1..50`
  - `cursor` optional opaque token
  - `kind` optional enum: `all`, `movie`, `actor` (default `all`)

REQ-TF-2 Response schema
- Success code: `200`
- Body:
  - `items`: array of feed records
  - `nextCursor`: string or `null`
- Item fields:
  - `id` (number)
  - `kind` (`movie` | `actor`)
  - `title` (string)
  - `summary` (string)
  - `body` (string)
  - `movieId` (number|null)
  - `actorName` (string|null)
  - `imageUrl` (string|null)
  - `featured` (boolean)
  - `publishAt` (ISO-8601)

REQ-TF-3 Ordering and pagination
- Feed order MUST be deterministic: `publishAt DESC`, then `id DESC`.
- Pagination MUST be keyset/cursor-based, not offset-based.
- `nextCursor` MUST represent the last record from current page.
- Requesting next page with returned cursor MUST not duplicate already returned rows.

REQ-TF-4 Content visibility
- Only active and currently valid content is returned:
  - `is_active = true`
  - `publish_at <= now`
  - `expire_at is null OR expire_at > now`

REQ-TF-5 Filtering
- `kind=movie` returns only movie news.
- `kind=actor` returns only actor news.
- `kind=all` returns both.

REQ-TF-6 Validation/error behavior
- Invalid `limit`, invalid `kind`, or malformed `cursor` returns `400` with JSON error.
- Unexpected backend failures return `500` using existing global error behavior.

REQ-TF-7 Client parity requirement
- Contract must remain client-neutral and stable for both Angular WebUI and Swift iOS consumption.
- Any contract field change requires update note in README and consumers.

Database requirements

REQ-TF-DB-1 New table
- Add table `timeline_content` in booking DB.

REQ-TF-DB-2 Columns
- `id` BIGINT/INT PK
- `kind` VARCHAR (enum domain: movie/actor)
- `title` VARCHAR
- `summary` VARCHAR
- `body` TEXT
- `movie_id` INT NULL
- `actor_name` VARCHAR NULL
- `image_url` VARCHAR NULL
- `featured` BOOLEAN default false
- `publish_at` TIMESTAMP
- `expire_at` TIMESTAMP NULL
- `is_active` BOOLEAN default true
- `created_at` TIMESTAMP
- `updated_at` TIMESTAMP

REQ-TF-DB-3 Indexes
- Index for timeline scan: `(is_active, publish_at DESC, id DESC)`
- Index for kind filter: `(kind, is_active, publish_at DESC, id DESC)`

REQ-TF-DB-4 Migration seed
- Provide initial seed rows for both `movie` and `actor` kinds to enable endpoint verification.

Architecture boundaries
- `BookController`: parse query params, call service, format response.
- `BookingHandlerImpl`: business logic, cursor decode/encode orchestration.
- `DAO`: keyset query and DB interactions.

Non-functional requirements

REQ-TF-NF-1 Performance
- Default page query should complete under 250 ms on local/minikube baseline data.

REQ-TF-NF-2 Observability
- Expose request metrics (count/latency) for endpoint.
- Log `limit`, `kind`, `cursorPresent`, `resultCount`.

REQ-TF-NF-3 Determinism
- Same dataset and same cursor must produce stable ordering and results.

REQ-TF-NF-4 Security
- Cursor parsing MUST reject malformed or tampered tokens with `400` and no stack trace leakage.
- Response MUST expose only defined API fields (no internal DB-only columns).

REQ-TF-NF-5 Performance validation
- Include a lightweight load/stress verification for cursor pagination (first page and deep page).

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] `GET /rest/book/timeline-feed` returns newest-first items with `nextCursor`.
- [ ] Cursor-based pagination returns non-overlapping pages.
- [ ] Filters (`all`, `movie`, `actor`) work correctly.
- [ ] Invalid cursor/params return `400` JSON error.
- [ ] Only active, publishable, non-expired content is returned.
- [ ] New DB table and indexes exist in booking DB migration.
- [ ] Endpoint contract is documented in `mbooks-quarkus/README.md` with curl examples.

Definition of Done
- [ ] Feature has spec, implementation, and tests completed.
- [ ] `@testing-engineer` verification completed.
- [ ] `@security-specialist` verification completed.
- [ ] `@performance-engineer` verification completed.

